Package structures.vectors

Interface Vector<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Generic Type
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataStructure<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    List<T>, Queue<E>, Stack<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayList, ArrayQueue, ArrayStack, LinkedList, LinkedQueue, LinkedStack

    public interface Vector<T>
extends DataStructure<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Interface for all linear DataStructures such as LinkedList, ArrayList, or any other vector-like data structure.

    • Method Detail

      • asString

        default java.lang.String asString​()
        Returns a String representation of the Vector. This function is named asString() rather than toString() because this is an interface, and thus toString() cannot be implemented as a default method because the superclass Object already implements it. Therefore, only a concrete class can override it. However, the implementation for all Vectors will be roughly the same. So we declare asString() as a wrapper around toString() so we avoid having to implement toString() in each subclass that implements this interface.
        Returns:
        String representation of the Vector
